Germany's World Cup-winning captain and former coach Franz Beckenbauer has said he made a "mistake" in the bidding process to host the 2006 World Cup, but denied that votes were bought.Beckenbauer was the head of the World Cup organising committee, which reports allege made a payment to Fifa in return for a financial grant.The 70-year-old said a Fifa proposal "should have been rejected".Germany beat South Africa in 2000 to host the tournament six years later.Beckenbauer added that he took "responsibility for this mistake".